## Instructions for using the library in your other project:

**1. Link the library in your other project:**
```bash
cd /path/to/your-other-project
npm link @jwtpro/jwt-client-js
```

**2. Import and use it in your code:**
```javascript
import { JWTPro } from '@jwtpro/jwt-client-js';

// Create client instance
const client = new JWTPro({
  baseUrl: 'https://your-wordpress-site.com/wp-json'
});

// Use it
try {
  const userData = await client.login('username', 'password');
  console.log('Logged in:', userData);

  const isValid = await client.validate(); // This now uses the correct endpoint!
  console.log('Token valid:', isValid);
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Auth error:', error);
}
```

**3. When you're done testing:**
```bash
npm unlink @jwtpro/jwt-client-js
```

That's it! The library is now available in your other project with the fixed validate endpoint.

